                  <msContents>
                     <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85045106 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104964" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_71-part2-item1">
                        <locus from="43r" to="123v">ff. 43r-123v</locus>
                        <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21786">Akhlāq-i Muḥsinīn</title>
                        <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21786">اخلاق محسنين</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Incomplete fragment of the treatise on ethics for rulers, entitled <title>Akhlāq-i Muḥsinī</title> (here written with a nassal ending), probably by <persName key="person_f7209" role="att">Kamāl al-Dīn Ḥusayn Vāʿiẓ Kāshifī Bayhaqī</persName>
                           </p>
                           <p>The work consists of forty bābs, but here ends abruptly in the thirty-third bāb </p>
                           <p>Defective at beginning and end
</p>
                           <p>Not dated
</p>
                           <p>Note (f. 43r), top left corner, stating the work was purchased with the aid of a certain Muḥammad Karīm Allāh
</p>
                           <p>Replacement leafs (ff. 43-45) in neater and more legible shikastah āmīz hand than the older portion, which s in a more mannered, awkward naskh
</p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
